COMMENDATIONS: Commends Malcolm "Coldblooded" Lee on being named Louisiana
Outstanding Log Truck Driver of the Year
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Malcolm "Coldblooded" Lee on being named Louisiana Outstanding Log
3 Truck Driver of the Year.
4 WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Malcolm "Coldblooded" Lee for his
5 dedication to safe and efficient log truck driving practices in northeast Louisiana and to
6 commend him on being named Louisiana Outstanding Log Truck Driver of the Year; and
7 WHEREAS, log truck drivers move timber from forest land to mills for processing
8 and are a vital part of the Louisiana logging industry; and
9 WHEREAS, log truck drivers spend countless hours on the road, navigating through
10 rural communities, school zones, and congested roadways, and they are always focused on
11 recognizing the potential for accidents and ensuring the safety of the public and their
12 truckloads and equipment; and
13 WHEREAS, without log truck drivers, the logging industry would not exist, and the
14 forests of Louisiana would become overgrown and unproductive; log truck drivers also
15 contribute significantly to local economies by purchasing parts, fuel, and lubricants; they
16 also support charitable causes and community needs; and
17 WHEREAS, log truck drivers face a variety of day-to-day issues, including inclimate
18 weather, a volatile market, and equipment failures; these problems often result in long work
19 hours, and drivers rely on their faith and family to overcome them; and
